DOW JONES U.S. FOOTWEAR INDEX

THE DOW JONES U.S. FOOTWEAR INDEX CONSISTS OF NIKE, DECKERS OUTDOOR CORP., TIMBERLAND CO., WOLVERINE WORLD

WIDE, INC., AND CROCS, INC. BECAUSE NIKE IS PART OF THE DOW JONES U.S. FOOTWEAR INDEX, THE PRICE AND RETURNS OF NIKE STOCK HAVE A SUBSTANTIAL EFFECT ON THIS INDEX. THE STANDARD & POORS APPAREL, ACCESSORIES & LUXURY GOODS

INDEX CONSISTS OF VF CORP., COACH, INC., AND POLO RALPH LAUREN CORPORATION. THE DOW JONES U.S. FOOTWEAR INDEX AND THE STANDARD & POORS APPAREL, ACCESSORIES, AND LUXURY GOODS INDEX INCLUDE COMPANIES IN TWO MAJOR LINES OF BUSINESS IN

WHICH THE COMPANY COMPETES. THE INDICES DO NOT ENCOMPASS ALL OF THE COMPANYS COMPETITORS, NOR ALL PRODUCT CATEGORIES AND LINES OF BUSINESS IN WHICH THE COMPANY IS ENGAGED.

