IN FISCAL 2008, WE ESTIMATE THAT THE COMBINATION OF FAVORABLE TRANSLATION OF FOREIGN CURRENCY-DENOMINATED

PROFITS FROM INTERNATIONAL BUSINESSES AND THE FOREIGN CURRENCY CONVERSION LOSSES INCLUDED IN OTHER (INCOME) EXPENSE, NET RESULTED IN A YEAR-OVER-YEAR INCREASE IN CONSOLIDATED INCOME BEFORE INCOME TAXES OF APPROXIMATELY $122 MILLION.

