THE INCREASE IN PRE-TAX INCOME FOR FISCAL 2008 VERSUS THE PRIOR YEAR WAS PRIMARILY ATTRIBUTABLE TO HIGHER

REVENUES, IMPROVED GROSS MARGINS AND OPERATING OVERHEAD LEVERAGE, COMBINED WITH FAVORABLE FOREIGN CURRENCY TRANSLATION. THESE FACTORS WERE PARTIALLY OFFSET BY HIGHER DEMAND CREATION SPENDING AS A PERCENTAGE OF REVENUE. THE GROSS MARGIN IMPROVEMENT

WAS DRIVEN PRIMARILY BY HIGHER IN-LINE NET PRICING MARGINS RESULTING FROM A BETTER MIX OF PRODUCTS SOLD AND FEWER DISCOUNTS OFFERED IN FISCAL 2008 COMPARED TO FISCAL 2007. THE INCREASE IN DEMAND CREATION SPENDING DURING FISCAL 2008 WAS PRIMARILY

ATTRIBUTABLE TO INVESTMENTS IN SPORTS MARKETING, MOST NOTABLY IN SOCCER, BRAND EVENTS AND INVESTMENTS IN OUR RETAIL PRESENTATION.

